bug.short_desc: Multiple windows are opened when one clicks on the same Event more than once

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0pre) Gecko/20110405 Thunderbird/3.3a4pre
I found this while debugging with DOM inspector, I clicked on the event twice, hoping to find the the same window to be brought to focused instead, i had to face the music of multiple event summary and editing windows opened at the same time.
Can someone confirm with me on this for a windows build as well.
Reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1.Open Thunderbird with Lightning installed 2.Create an Event 3.Click on the Event 4.Now focus away from the window (Dont Close it) and click the event again Actual Results: 1.TB opens another dialog box for the same event
Expected Results: 1.TB should have focused back to the same dialog box
and if one tries to edit the event information, the dialog box returns an error saying that update failed.

Created attachment 524225 Multiple opened windows for the same event in TB
Attachment for the multiple event summary window issue.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 373251 ***
